<h1>Macro Library construct2</h1>
<p>Construct2 integration functions, Version 0.1, Dec 18, 2013</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#addConstruct2">addConstruct2</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="addConstruct2"><a name="addConstruct2">addConstruct2</a></h3>
<p><strong>addConstruct2(url, [width, height, params, qn, part])</strong></p>
<p>Places a Construct2 HTML5 applet, using the HTML file specified in <code>url</code>. The applet must have the IMathAS <code>postMessage</code> shim added to the scripts.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>params</strong>: a key=&gt;value array of values to send to Construct2 via the query string, like <code>array('a'=>3,'name'=>'Fred')</code>. These will be readable in Construct2 using <code>Browser.QueryParam("name")</code>.</li>
<li><strong>qn, part</strong>: if you want to read values from Construct2, provide the question number (1-indexed - usually use <code>$thisq</code>), and if multipart, the part number (0-indexed). IMathAS doesn't request values - Construct2 has to send them.</li>
</ul>
<p>Use <code>Browser.QueryParam("imathasqn")</code> to read the IMathAS question number, then form a return string text variable like <code>imathasqn&"::"&myvar&","&anothervar</code> to send back. To send it, use Browser -&gt; Execute Javascript like this: <code>"parent.postMessage('"&returnstring&"','*')"</code>.</p>
<p>See <a href="http://www.imathas.com/misc/basicimathasex.capx">http://www.imathas.com/misc/basicimathasex.capx</a> for an example.</p>
<details class="example"><summary>Examples</summary><pre>addConstruct2("myapplet.html", 640, 480, array('a'=>3, 'name'=>'Fred'), $thisq)</pre></details>
</body></html>
